
Visual Semantics


This assignment focuses on using visual methods to represent semantic relationships. 

This is a real-world example from JP Morgan Chase’s web site, which contains information about the bank’s businesses, 
services and customers. 

The goal is to create a visual representation of these data that shows how the components of this large holding company 
are organized.


Instructions

Create a clear visual infographic of JP Morgan Chase and its businesses - using the bullet points below as your data. 

The work should communicate the textual data visually to provide a succinct and interesting picture of the JP Morgan company.   


Data

Direct citation from the JP Morgan Chase Website: 
https://www.jpmorganchase.com/corporate/About-JPMC/about-us.htm (Links to an external site.)


Information need to be included in the visual infographic:

1. We are a leading global financial services firm with assets of $2.6 trillion.
2. We operate in more than 60 countries. We have over 240,000 employees.
3. We serve millions of consumers, small businesses and many of the world's most prominent corporate, 
4. institutional and government clients.
5. We are a leader in investment banking, financial services for consumers and small businesses, commercial banking, 
financial transaction processing and asset management.
6.Our stock is a component of the Dow Jones Industrial Average"
